The paper deals with graph invariants and canonization, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of parallel computation suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the application of the results to graph classes with bounded treewidth suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG), as treewidth is often used as a measure of the complexity of graphical models in this field.
